* Iron Raptor had a hunch that something was happening here that she 
couldn't even begin to try and work out, but she also had an idea that Prowl 
was going through the same thing as she was. So at least she wouldn't have 
to figure all of this out on her own.
Besides, she also was sure that Prowl knew a hell of a lot more then she did 
about all this, and maybe could fill her in on a few things to help her 
understand.

But Iron Raptor watched him nod after she spoke his name, not use to this 
body and its speaking abilities.
Though, as she watched him lean closer to her, she suddenly felt...felt that 
everything would be all right. Even though it all seemed so strange.

The sound of Prowls voice answering her relaxed what tensions she had, her 
eyes following him as he kneeled down beside her.
Watching Prowl as he ran his hand through her hair, just sitting and 
watching.
So much had happened, and she was only catching up. Tilting her head towards 
Prowls hand, her mind asking a million questions.
But she only spoke two.*

" What are we, and how did this happen?"
